cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the automated construction of a reactive system from a high-level description expressed in LTLf, which is a logic language. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the conversion of LTLf formulas to DFAs, which involves programming language concepts such as automata and state-space representation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper deals with the synthesis of reactive systems, which is a software engineering problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with automated construction of systems, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with automata and their conversion from LTLf formulas.
